latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Its World  Dance day . I want to share with you a story about my relationship with dance . I came back from Nyc just then , and was leaving bombay to come to Bangalore. It was a very very difficult phase in my life . I remember that time so vividly. I questioned everything that happened in my life then and the only time i got some relief was when I rehearsed for this piece for two hours for three days . I forgot about my pain and was transported to a safe haven of joy and bliss. And then i shot this video. I remember having tears of joy and a sense of peace and liberation. Dance healed a lot of my pain then and dance still does that to me . My relationship with dance is so sacred and i feel gratitude for this relationship . So for anyone feeling down and out , dance it out darling.. its your magic potion for your soul ❤️

Thank you for this piece @madammovement . Forever grateful ❤️
Shot by : @meghnabhalla

My last sunset in Bali. Ten soul nourishing days.  Natarajasana , in the golden light is my way of saying thank you. Thank you, Bali, for the peace, the magic, the stillness. My heart is full. I’ll be back soon ✨🤍

#yogi #sunset #gratitude #wholesome

From beach days to dance nights, spontaneous adventures to slow sunsets , Bali gave us memories we’ll never forget. Grateful for every laugh, every moment, and for doing it all with my soul sister by my side. Here’s to friendship, freedom, and finding joy in the little things ❤️🌺 #Balivibe #bali #bestiereels #memorylane
